title: Grateful Dead Live at Winterland Arena on 1978-10-20
lineage: Nakamichi CR3A w/ Dolby > Audigy 4 Pro @ 24/44.1 > Editing with NERO > Tracked With CD Wave > Dithered to 16 bit with Audacity > Flac (level 8)
description:
Set 1

Minglewood Blues, They Love Each Other, Cassidy, Dire Wolf, El Paso, Tennessee Jed, It's All Over Now, Loser, Lazy Lightning > Supplication

Set 2

Mississippi Half-Step Uptown Toodeloo > Franklin's Tower, Dancin' In The Streets > Drums > Space > Not Fade Away > Black Peter > Around & Around 

E1: Johnny B. Goode 

E2: Shakedown Street

reviews.review_text: best source for this show Attention Dead fans!  You want this version of this great show.  Better sound than the Holwein recording. Complete, good levels, low hiss. The performance is wonderful.  Set 2 pre-drums in particular. This recording puts you right on the floor of the Winterland with the party people, enjoy.

End of Cassidy concert-goer Conversation  Lol at the end of Cassidy there is this hilarious moment where you overhear two people discuss the price of 5 grams, followed by some other guy who mentioned "Looks like a chunk of hash to me."  Ya you could say it feels like i'm at a dead show, so 5 stars
